President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of North Carolina following a tornado and severe storms on April 15, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically Guilford and Rockingham counties. The assistance includes grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid individuals and business owners in recovering from the disaster. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be funded on a cost-sharing basis. Elizabeth A. Turner has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance through the DisasterAssistance.gov website or by calling the toll-free numbers provided.